headline: 3 Reasons FFIV is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Even during a down period for the markets, F5 has gone against the grain, climbing to $266. Its shares have yielded a 21.7% return over the last six months, beating the S&P 500 by 23.4%. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
